<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Actual FC (FrontController) stands like</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$router = $this-&gt;getRouter();
$router-&gt;setParams($this-&gt;getParams());

// ...

 try {
            $this-&gt;_plugins-&gt;routeStartup($this-&gt;_request);
            $router-&gt;route($this-&gt;_request);
            // ....
</code></pre>

<p>As you can see, there is no way for a plugin listening on routeStartup() to alter the router in FrontController as it's already been set before.</p>

<p>We should find a way to allow that, like, for example, move the $router affectation just after the routeStartup routine</p>

